HumChaosProject — Line-by-line Explanation
=========================================

This document explains what each line does and why it exists.
Files covered:
- src/main.js
- src/vertex.glsl
- src/fragment.glsl

------------------------------------------------------------
1) src/main.js
------------------------------------------------------------

1. `import * as THREE from 'three';`
   - What: Imports the Three.js library namespace.
   - Why: Needed to create renderer, scene, camera, geometry, and shader material.

2. `import vertexShader from './vertex.glsl?raw';`
   - What: Imports vertex shader source as a plain string.
   - Why: `ShaderMaterial` requires raw GLSL source.

3. `import fragmentShader from './fragment.glsl?raw';`
   - What: Imports fragment shader source as a plain string.
   - Why: This shader contains the raymarching Mandelbulb logic.

4. (blank)
   - What: Visual separation.
   - Why: Improves readability.

5. `const app = document.querySelector('#app');`
   - What: Finds the default Vite root element.
   - Why: Starter template injects UI there; we replace it with full-screen canvas.

6. `if (app) app.remove();`
   - What: Removes Vite starter DOM if it exists.
   - Why: Prevents overlaying starter content over rendered shader.

7. (blank)

8. `const renderer = new THREE.WebGLRenderer({ antialias: true, powerPreference: 'high-performance' });`
   - What: Creates WebGL renderer.
   - Why: Required for GPU rendering; options improve edge quality and performance hint.

9. `renderer.setPixelRatio(Math.min(window.devicePixelRatio, 2));`
   - What: Caps render pixel density.
   - Why: Balances sharpness and performance on high-DPI screens.

10. `renderer.setSize(window.innerWidth, window.innerHeight);`
    - What: Sets canvas size to full window.
    - Why: Full-screen visual output.

11. `document.body.style.margin = '0';`
    - What: Removes page margin.
    - Why: Ensures no white borders around canvas.

12. `document.body.style.overflow = 'hidden';`
    - What: Disables scrollbars.
    - Why: Keeps immersive full-screen output clean.

13. `document.body.appendChild(renderer.domElement);`
    - What: Adds the WebGL canvas to the page.
    - Why: Makes rendering visible.

14. (blank)

15. `const scene = new THREE.Scene();`
    - What: Creates a scene container.
    - Why: Three.js renderer expects scene graph structure.

16. `const camera = new THREE.OrthographicCamera(-1, 1, 1, -1, 0, 1);`
    - What: Creates orthographic camera sized for clip-space quad.
    - Why: For full-screen shader passes, no perspective geometry camera needed.

17. (blank)

18. `const uniforms = {`
    - What: Starts shader uniform object.
    - Why: Uniforms pass changing data from JS to GLSL.

19. `  u_time: { value: 0 },`
    - What: Time uniform.
    - Why: Drives animation in shader.

20. `  u_resolution: { value: new THREE.Vector2(window.innerWidth, window.innerHeight) },`
    - What: Screen resolution uniform.
    - Why: Keeps aspect ratio and pixel-space aware effects correct.

21. `  u_cameraPos: { value: new THREE.Vector3(0, 0, 5) },`
    - What: Initial ray origin.
    - Why: Needed for camera-space ray construction in fragment shader.

22. `  u_cameraTarget: { value: new THREE.Vector3(0, 0, 0) },`
    - What: Initial look-at target.
    - Why: Needed to compute camera basis vectors.

23. `};`
    - What: Ends uniform object.
    - Why: Required syntax.

24. (blank)

