    - Why: `mapScene` signature requires `out` param.

77. `  vec2 e = vec2(HIT_EPS, 0.0);`
    - What: Small epsilon vector.
    - Why: Used for finite differences.

78. `  return normalize(vec3(`
79. `    mapScene(p + e.xyy, t) - mapScene(p - e.xyy, t),`
80. `    mapScene(p + e.yxy, t) - mapScene(p - e.yxy, t),`
81. `    mapScene(p + e.yyx, t) - mapScene(p - e.yyx, t)`
82. `  ));`
    - What: Central-difference gradient.
    - Why: Gradient direction approximates surface normal.

83. `}`
    - What: Ends function.

84. (blank)

85. `void buildCameraBasis(in vec3 ro, in vec3 ta, out vec3 f, out vec3 r, out vec3 u){`
    - What: Starts camera basis builder.
    - Why: Converts camera position/target into orthonormal axes.

86. `  f = normalize(ta - ro);`
    - What: Forward vector.
    - Why: Ray direction base toward target.

87. `  r = normalize(cross(vec3(0.0, 1.0, 0.0), f));`
    - What: Right vector.
    - Why: Horizontal axis from world up and forward.

88. `  u = cross(f, r);`
    - What: Up vector.
    - Why: Completes orthonormal camera frame.

89. `}`
    - What: Ends function.

