96. `  vec3 ta = u_cameraTarget;`
    - What: Sets look target from uniform.
    - Why: Defines forward direction.

97. (blank)

98. `  vec3 f, r, u;`
    - What: Declares basis vectors.
    - Why: Used to build world ray direction.

99. `  buildCameraBasis(ro, ta, f, r, u);`
    - What: Computes camera frame.
    - Why: Converts screen coord to world ray.

100. (blank)

101. `  vec3 rd = normalize(uv.x * r + uv.y * u + 1.9 * f);`
     - What: Computes ray direction.
     - Why: Perspective-like projection from camera basis.

102. (blank)

103. `  float dTravel = 0.0;`
     - What: Initializes marched distance.
     - Why: Ray starts at origin.

104. `  float d = 0.0;`
     - What: Current distance sample.
     - Why: Stores SDF/DE value per step.

105. `  float trap = 0.0;`
     - What: Current trap value.
