------------------------------------------------------------
Notes for your assignment framing
------------------------------------------------------------
- Predictable order:
  - The camera path uses deterministic sine/cosine equations.
  - The shader runs fixed update rules every frame.
- Unpredictable/chaotic expression:
  - Iterated fractal feedback amplifies tiny changes over time.
  - Animated exponent and subtle rotational warp continuously alter topology.
- Why both coexist:
  - Strict mathematics creates emergent complexity; rules are stable, outcomes are rich.
